Project Overview

This repository contains three Java console-based applications developed to demonstrate object-oriented programming concepts, user interaction, conditional statements, loops, and basic Java programming.

Project 1: Guessing Number Game

Objective:

To create a game where the user guesses a randomly generated number within a limited number of attempts.

Features:
Random number generation
User input validation
Hints (Higher/Lower)
Limited attempts
Displays win/loss message

Concepts Used: 
Random class
Loops
Conditional statements
Scanner class

Project 2: Student Grade Calculator

Objective:

To calculate the total marks, average percentage, and grade based on the marks entered by the user.

Features:
Accepts marks for multiple subjects
Calculates total marks
Calculates average percentage
Assigns grade based on percentage

Concepts Used:
Arrays
Loops
Conditional statements
Scanner class

Project 3: ATM Interface

Objective:

To simulate an ATM system that allows users to perform basic banking operations.

Features:
Check account balance
Deposit money
Withdraw money
Exit the application

Concepts Used:
Classes and Objects
Methods
Switch statement
Scanner class

GitHub Repository:

https://github.com/sowmya-220803/java

Conclusion:

These Java projects helped in understanding core Java concepts such as classes, objects, loops, conditional statements, arrays, methods, and user interaction through console-based applications. Git and GitHub were used for version control and project management.